# Structure Rules

Hierarchy (3D Graph):

Phase (state container) ─┬─ Sequential dependency (blocking)
├─ Task (transformer) │
│ └─ Subtask (atomic) └─ Lateral connections (non-blocking)
└─ Diagonal dependencies (task-to-task across phases)

PHASE:

[ ] = pending (not started)
[x] = complete (verified)

Phase States:

0% = blocked (dependencies incomplete)
1-99% = active (in progress)
100% ✅ = complete (all tasks verified)

Phase Transition Triggers (Explicit Unlocking):

N = 1
phase(N).state = "complete" ↔ phase(N).progress === 100%
phase(N+1).unlocked ↔ phase(N).state === "complete" AND
phase(N).outgoing_edges.all_satisfied

outgoing_edge.satisfied ↔ target_phase.dependencies_met OR
target_phase.dependency_type === "lateral" (non-blocking)

---

# Template Variables

- `{TASK_NAME}`: System identifier
- `{DATE}`: ISO-8601 date
- `{PHASE_N_GOAL}`: Phase objective
- `{VERIFICATION_CMD}`: Verification command
- `{NARRATIVE}`: Causal story connecting phases
- `{LATERAL_DEPS}`: Cross-phase connections

